    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Morphine gel applied topically to wounds will reduce wound pain and decrease patients use of
      oral and intravenous pain medications, therefore reducing side effects.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients will be randomized to receive either placebo (versa base gel) or morphine gel to
      wound. Patients receiving morphine gel will have a decrease in pain score and use less
      oral/intravenous pain medications.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
